weighed%20on%20domestic%20firms'%20margins%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Falembic-pharma-q3-result-profit-dips-23-to-rs-138-cr-on-weak-sales-125020300847_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20DeepSeek%20Shows%20Why%20Nandan%20Nilekani%20Is%20Right%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20wants%20to%20deploy%20huge%20amounts%20of%20capital%20and%20resources%20to%20build%20its%20own%20models%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20(AI)%20to%20compete%20with%20global%20firms%2C%20and%20finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20just%20gave%20the%20idea%20a%20more%20than%201%2C000%25%20backing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIT%20minister%20Ashwini%20Vaishnaw%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbctv18.com%2Ftechnology%2Findia-ai-foundational-model-like-chatgpt-deepseek-gemini-to-be-ready-in-10-months-says-ashwini-vaishnaw-19548924.htm%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20that%20half%20a%20dozen%20startups%20were%20working%20on%20a%20foundational%20AI%20model%20for%20India%20and%20it%20would%20be%20ready%20within%20eight%20to%2010%20months.%20India%20had%20procured%20about%2018%2C600%20high-end%20graphic%20processing%20units%2C%20including%20Nvidia's%20Hoppers%2C%20for%20them.%20Vaishnaw's%20announcement%20had%20an%20edge%20of%20urgency%20after%20Chinese%20startup%20DeepSeek%20created%20a%20minor%20earthquake%20in%20the%20AI%20world%20with%20its%20ridiculously%20cost-efficient%20model%2C%20R1.%20Minister%20Sitharaman%20raised%20the%20budgetary%20allocation%20for%20the%20national%20AI%20Mission%20to%20Rs%202%2C000%20crore%20from%20Rs%20173%20crore%20last%20year%2C%20much%20of%20which%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20directed%20at%20building%20Large%20Language%20Models%20(LLMs).%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Bharat%20OS%20Experience%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20past%20efforts%20at%20indigenously%20designing%20and%20making%20foundational%20technology%20building%20blocks%2C%20such%20as%20a%20home-grown%20operating%20system%20(Bharat%20OS)%2C%20went%20nowhere.%20The%20system%20was%20buggy%20and%20efforts%20to%20popularise%20it%20were%20largely%20stymied.%20Tech%20systems%20often%20improve%20with%20use%2C%20but%20BOS%20never%20got%20a%20shot%20at%20it.%20India's%20efforts%20to%20produce%20semiconductors%2C%20despite%20first%20embarking%20on%20it%20via%20a%20cabinet%20decision%20in%201976%20to%20set%20up%20the%20Semiconductor%20Complex%20Ltd%2C%20never%20really%20took%20off%20despite%20trying%20to%20lure%20global%20leaders%20with%20massive%20incentives.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20private%20entrepreneurial%20attempts%20at%20replicating%20globally%20popular%20tech%20products%20or%20services%2C%20such%20as%20short-video%20apps%2C%20a%20la%20TikTok%2C%20or%20a%20Twitter%20clone%2C%20only%20ended%20up%20burning%20millions%20of%20venture%20funds.%20India%20has%20typically%20achieved%20scaling%20up%20of%20local%20products%20by%20erecting%20tariff%20walls%2C%20the%20latest%20case%20in%20point%20being%20homegrown%20wearables%20companies%20making%20headphones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20track%20record%20suggests%20that%20building%20AI%20models%20could%20also%20run%20up%20against%20scaling%20and%20capital%20challenges.%20A%20better%20strategy%20might%20be%20what%20Infosys%20co-founder%20Nandan%20Nilekani%20proposed%20last%20year.%20Nilekani%20said%20that%20India%20should%20not%20waste%20time%20building%20another%20LLM%20or%20Large%20Language%20Model%2C%20a%20kind%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20that%20can%20speak%20the%20human%20language%2C%20the%20most%20popular%20one%20being%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT.%20%E2%80%9CLet%20the%20big%20boys%20in%20the%20(Silicon)%20Valley%20do%20it%2C%20spending%20billions%20of%20dollars.%20We%20will%20use%20it%20to%20create%20synthetic%20data%2C%20build%20small%20language%20models%20quickly%2C%20and%20train%20them%20using%20appropriate%20data%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nilekani%20said.%20He%20is%20right.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20India%20Do%20An%20IT%20Encore%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENilekani%20has%20seen%20the%20trajectory%20of%20the%20Indian%20software%20industry%20and%20what%20India%20is%20capable%20of.%20He%20was%20there%20when%20it%20was%20birthed%20by%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%2C%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20and%20Sam%20Pitroda.%20Pitroda%20has%20recounted%20how%20he%20convinced%20Jack%20Welch%2C%20the%20then%20chief%20of%20General%20Electric%2C%20to%20hire%20Indian%20companies%20to%20write%20software%20for%20the%20multinational%20giant.%20The%20first%20contract%20was%20worth%20%2410%20million.%20It%20spawned%20an%20industry%20that%20exported%20software%20services%20worth%20%24205%20billion%20in%202024.%20The%20IT%20industry%20employs%20about%205.4%20million%20people.%20It%20formed%20the%20bedrock%20of%20the%20modern%20Indian%20economic%20miracle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20slim%20chance%2C%20if%20it%20plays%20its%20cards%20right%2C%20that%20India%20can%20do%20an%20encore%2C%20as%20AI%20will%20transfer%20the%20power%20of%20programming%20to%20anyone%20with%20an%20LLM.%20It%20could%20also%20be%20the%20disruption%20that%20rips%20apart%20the%20country's%20socio-economic%20fabric%20with%20rampant%20joblessness%20and%20social%20inequality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Spectre%20Of%20Automation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20NBER%20(National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research)%20paper%20titled%20%3Cem%3ETechnological%20Disruption%20in%20the%20Labor%20Market%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20economists%20David%20J.%20Deming%2C%20Christopher%20Ong%2C%20and%20Lawrence%20H.%20Summers%20wrote%20that%20AI%20could%20be%20a%20general-purpose%20technology%20on%20the%20scale%20of%20prior%20disruptive%20innovations%2C%20such%20as%20steam%20and%20electricity.%20The%20economists%2C%20who%20crunched%20US%20labour%20data%20going%20back%20to%201880%2C%20found%20that%20the%20years%20spanning%201990%20to%202017%20were%20less%20disruptive%20than%20any%20prior%20period.%20However%2C%20the%20illusion%20of%20a%20stable%20labour%20market%20in%20that%20period%20is%20because%20the%20past%20changes%20were%20too%20profound.%20They%20found%20that%20low-%20and%20middle-paid%20jobs%20have%20dwindled%2C%20while%20high-paying%20professional%20and%20technical%20work%20has%20increased.%20US%20retail%20sales%20jobs%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20have%20shrunk%20by%2025%25%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20while%20science%2C%20technology%2C%20engineering%20and%20math%20jobs'%20share%20in%20the%20overall%20pie%20rose%20from%206.5%25%20in%202010%20to%2010%25%20in%202014.%20This%20shift%20happened%20with%20automation.%20The%20authors%20are%20yet%20to%20study%20the%20impact%20of%20LLMs%20as%20it%20is%20too%20early.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoldman%20Sachs%20CEO%2C%20David%20Solomon%2C%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20recently%20that%20AI%20can%20complete%2095%25%20of%20the%20initial%20documentation%20for%20an%20IPO%2C%20a%20two-week%20task%20for%20a%20six-person%20team%2C%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20minutes.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20last%205%25%20now%20matters%20because%20the%20rest%20is%20now%20a%20commodity%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Automation%2C%20robotics%2C%20and%20now%20general%20AI%20will%20combine%20to%20eliminate%20millions%20of%20jobs%20that%20were%20pathways%20for%20upward%20economic%20mobility.%20The%20domino%20effect%20of%20automation%20is%20already%20reflected%20in%20the%20dwindling%20number%20of%20skilled%20workers%20such%20as%20fitters%2C%20welders%2C%20and%20painters%20on%20shop%20floors.%20The%20World%20Bank%20predicted%20as%20far%20back%20as%202016%20that%20automation%20would%20take%20away%2069%25%20of%20jobs%20in%20India%20and%2077%25%20in%20China.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20traditional%20economic%20path%20from%20increasing%20productivity%20of%20agriculture%20to%20light%20manufacturing%20and%20then%20to%20full-scale%20industrialisation%20may%20not%20be%20possible%20for%20all%20developing%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jim%20Yong%20Kim%2C%20then%20World%20Bank%20president%2C%20had%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELearn%20From%20The%20Past%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPast%20technological%20leaps%20have%20often%20produced%20more%20net%20jobs%20and%20better%20wages%20as%20they%20helped%20labour%20productivity%20and%20generated%20new%20tasks.%20Jobs%20growth%20in%20the%20post-war%20US%20was%20in%20large%20measure%20accounted%20for%20by%20occupations%20generating%20new%20tasks%2C%20economists%20Daron%20Acemoglu%20and%20Pascual%20Restrepo%20argued%20in%20a%202019%20paper.%20However%2C%20that%20trend%20is%20trailing%20off.%20Employment%20and%20wage%20growth%20suffered%20in%20the%20first%20two%20decades%20of%20this%20century%20as%20new%20tasks%20failed%20to%20materialise%2C%20they%20wrote.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%20Nilekani's%20suggestion%20has%20substantial%20merit.%20India%20needs%20to%20provide%20meaningful%20livelihoods%20to%20more%20people%20than%20any%20other%20country%20on%20the%20planet.%20It%20has%20limited%20resources%20to%20do%20that.%20The%20success%20of%20the%20software%20industry%20rested%20on%20familiarising%20millions%20of%20young%20Indians%20with%20modern%20computer%20systems%20and%20training%20them%20in%20coding%20languages.%20A%20training%20ecosystem%20led%20by%20institutes%20such%20as%20NIIT%20and%20Aptech%20quickly%20sprung%20up%2C%20creating%20a%20robust%20assembly%20line%20of%20professionals.%20Irrespective%20of%20the%20quality%20of%20their%20basic%20education%2C%20thousands%20of%20students%20who%20trained%20at%20these%20institutes%20helped%20meet%20the%20demand%20for%20skilled%20professionals%20when%20the%20Y2K%20scare%20drew%20near%20and%20global%20corporations%20needed%20armies%20of%20programmers%20to%20rewrite%20billions%20of%20lines%20of%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20requires%20a%20similar%20push%20to%20create%20a%20training%20ecosystem%20that%20can%20equip%20people%20to%20deal%20with%20data%20or%20new%20tasks%20in%20an%20AI%20world.%20As%20Nilekani%20said%2C%20India%20should%20not%20bother%20with%20building%20LLMs%20but%20focus%20on%20small%20language%20models.%20India%20can%20be%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20use%20case%20capital%20of%20AI%20globally%E2%80%9D.%20Chinese%20startup%20DeepSeek%20has%20shown%20that%20segments%20of%20the%20AI%20industry%20will%20soon%20get%20commoditised.%20It%20will%20ultimately%20boil%20down%20to%20cost.%20And%20India%20could%20yet%20be%20well%20positioned%20to%20eke%20out%20its%20comparative%20advantage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20can%20also%20use%20the%20predictive%20capabilities%20of%20AI%20models%20to%20assist%20decision-making%20at%20local%20levels%20of%20governance.%20For%20instance%2C%20AI%20can%20enable%20hyperlocal%20weather%20analysis%20to%20help%20farmers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia's%20Data%20Advantage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20leading%20generators%20of%20data.%20Billionaire%20Mukesh%20Ambani's%20telecom%20firm%20Jio%20delivered%2016%20exabytes%20of%20data%20in%20one%20year.%20Indians%20are%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20users%20of%20social%20media%2C%20OTT%2C%20and%20e-commerce%20platforms%20by%20volume.%20It%20has%20encouraged%20Ambani%20to%20join%20hands%20with%20Nvidia%20to%20build%20massive%20AI%20infrastructure%20in%20India%2C%20primarily%20data%20centres.%20If%20India%20generates%20such%20quantities%20of%20data%2C%20it%20should%20also%20have%20the%20capacity%20to%20process%20it%20by%20building%20a%20cohort%20of%20young%20workers%20with%20skills%20such%20as%20critical%20thinking%2C%20problem-solving%2C%20creativity%2C%20and%20emotional%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Dinesh%20Narayanan%20is%20a%20Delhi-based%20journalist%20and%20author%20of%20'The%20RSS%20And%20The%20Making%20Of%20The%20Deep%20Nation'.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%