2https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbosses-done-caring-worker-feelings-rto-wfh-cost-cutting-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emandate%20a%20return%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20for%20some%20Gen%20Zers%20who%20graduated%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20remote%20work%20may%20be%20all%20they%20have%20ever%20known%20in%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20may%20not%20be%20a%20one-size-fits-all%20approach%20to%20how%20to%20behave%20at%20the%20office%2C%20BI%20talked%20to%20etiquette%20experts%20to%20get%20their%20advice%20on%20smoothing%20the%20transition%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArden%20Clise%20of%20Clise%20Etiquette%20says%20the%20biggest%20complaint%20she's%20heard%20from%20clients%20is%20that%20workers%20need%20to%20brush%20up%20on%20their%20social%20skills%20and%20remember%20%26quot%3Bthe%20niceties%20that%20we%20can%20get%20into%20a%20habit%20of%20doing%20when%20we're%20spending%20more%20time%20with%20people%2C%20but%20have%20gotten%20forgotten%20when%20we're%20isolated%20in%20our%20homes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20whether%20you're%20re-entering%20the%20corporate%20office%20world%20after%20a%20few%20years%20of%20being%20remote%20or%20starting%20your%20first%20in-person%20job%2C%20here's%20a%20refresher%20on%20post-pandemic%20office%20etiquette.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226ac3ad49-260d-4e5a-a6e7-0d2e26d92e46%5C%22%3EBusiness%20attire%3A%20A%20little%20self%20awareness%20goes%20a%20long%20way%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-rto-policy-federal-employee-fashion-stylist-what-to-wear-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMany%20white-collar%20workers%20are%20dressing%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20casually%20when%20they%20return%20to%20the%20office%20today%20compared%20to%20pre-pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20I'm%20working%20with%20HR%20and%20companies%2C%20I%20see%20every%20one%20of%20them%20dusting%20off%20an%20old%20dress%20code%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lisa%20Richey%20of%20The%20American%20Academy%20of%20Etiquette.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Post%20Senning%20of%20The%20Emily%20Post%20Institute%20said%20it%20can%20be%20helpful%20to%20%26quot%3Bthink%20about%20what%20the%20floor%20of%20your%20formality%20is%20for%20a%20professional%20environment%20or%20interaction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20going%20to%20be%20different%20for%20different%20people%20in%20different%20industries%2C%20different%20jobs%2C%20different%20work%20cultures%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20making%20an%20effort%20to%20think%20about%20how%20you%20want%20to%20present%20professionally%20and%20setting%20some%20baseline%20standards%20for%20yourself%2C%20and%20then%20adhering%20to%20them%2C%20is%20a%20really%20good%20place%20to%20start.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20note%20of%20what%20your%20peers%20are%20wearing%20and%20consult%20your%20official%20dress%20code%20policy%20if%20your%20organization%20has%20one.%20In%20lieu%20of%20company%20guidance%2C%20you%20can%20ask%20what%20might%20be%20appropriate%20if%20you%20don't%20know%2C%20the%20experts%20advised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20your%20clothing%2C%20grooming%20and%20hygiene%20are%20also%20integral%20to%20how%20you%20present%20yourself%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20you%20choose%20to%20dress%20and%20present%20isn't%20just%20about%20personal%20expression%2C%20it's%20also%20about%20showing%20respect%20for%20the%20people%20and%20environments%20that%20you're%20operating%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Senning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a00732ad-556c-42be-9310-9aad89166c4a%5C%22%3EDon't%20get%20too%20personal%20when%20meeting%20a%20colleague%20in%20person%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20return%20to%20office%20means%20you%20might%20see%20a%20coworker%20in%20person%20for%20the%20first%20time%20after%20knowing%20them%20as%20a%20virtual%20head-and-shoulders%20for%20the%20past%20few%20years%20%E2%80%94%20or%20you%20might%20see%20a%20colleague%20again%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20perfectly%20appropriate%20to%20shake%20hands%20in%20either%20case%2C%20but%20be%20careful%20not%20to%20make%20insensitive%20comments%20about%20how%20someone%20might%20look%20different%20than%20you%20expected%2C%20or%20how%20a%20coworker's%20appearance%20might%20have%20changed%20since%20you%20last%20saw%20them%20in%20person%2C%20the%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaying%20a%20simple%20hello%20and%20goodbye%20when%20you%20come%20and%20go%20are%20easy%20%26quot%3B'gimme'%20social%20interactions%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Senning%20calls%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20cost%20you%20nothing%2C%20and%20done%20well%2C%20and%20repeatedly%2C%20they%20really%20forge%20important%20social%20bonds%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20build%20a%20sense%20of%20connection%20and%20trust%20that%20is%20going%20to%20carry%20you%20through%20tense%20meetings%2C%20critical%20feedback%2C%20miscommunications%2C%20things%20like%20that%20later%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22315ab257-eaae-4826-8ffe-c82e1e010a0a%5C%22%3EShared%20spaces%20are%20exactly%20that%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatt-begins-5-days-office-mandate-desks-parking-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehot-desking%2C%20where%20multiple%20workers%20share%20the%20same%20desk%20at%20different%20times%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20hot-desking%2C%20make%20sure%20you%20clean%20up%20before%20you%20leave%20and%20remove%20any%20of%20your%20personal%20items%20from%20the%20desk%20for%20the%20next%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20conference%20rooms%2C%20check%20in%20with%20your%20company's%20reservation%20system%20to%20make%20sure%20you're%20not%20using%20a%20room%20someone%20else%20has%20reserved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConflict%20can%20arise%20around%20a%20shared%20resource%20if%20people%20aren't%20taking%20a%20certain%20level%20of%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Senning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20on%20time%20is%20particularly%20important%20for%20in-person%20meetings%20as%20opposed%20to%20virtual%20ones%20because%20of%20the%20extra%20effort%20your%20colleagues%20made%20to%20get%20to%20the%20office%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20unlike%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frules-for-holding-successful-virtual-meetings-with-employees%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evirtual%20meetings%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20you%20might%20secretly%20give%20your%20attention%20to%20other%20browser%20windows%20or%20IRL%20happenings%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20you%20should%20put%20your%20phone%20away%20in%20an%20in-person%20meeting%20and%20give%20your%20fellow%20attendees%20your%20undivided%20attention.%20(If%20you%20don't%2C%20they'll%20certainly%20notice.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20age-old%20wisdom%20on%20avoiding%20fish%20at%20the%20office%20stands%2C%20says%20Clise.%20Remember%20to%20clean%20out%20anything%20you%20stored%20in%20the%20communal%20fridge%20periodically.%20And%20if%20you're%20taking%20the%20last%20cup%20of%20coffee%2C%20make%20a%20new%20pot%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20lunch%20in%20the%20breakroom%20or%20cafeteria%20versus%20at%20your%20desk%20to%20%26quot%3Bhave%20more%20opportunities%20to%20chat%20with%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20Clise%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20your%20office%20setup%2C%20you%20should%20also%20be%20careful%20to%20approach%20phone%20calls%20a%20certain%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20true%20for%20years%20that%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20complaints%20about%20coworkers'%20behavior%20in%20open%20office%20environments%20is%20people%20talking%20too%20loudly%20on%20phones%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Senning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20returning%20to%20the%20office%2C%20step%20away%20from%20your%20desk%20to%20take%20personal%20calls.%20Don't%20use%20speakerphone%20in%20a%20cubicle%20or%20open-plan%20office%3B%20you%20can%20if%20you%20have%20your%20own%20office%2C%20but%20close%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20able%20to%20project%20your%20voice%20at%20home%20versus%20working%20at%20an%20open%20space%20in%20an%20office%20is%20very%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Clise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c78618ee-66ce-4e74-9fa3-98d5975d7fa6%5C%22%3EAt%20social%20gatherings%2C%20you're%20still%20at%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-to-avoid-doing-work-happy-hour-etiquette-expert-tips%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHappy%20hours%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20learning%20lunches%2C%20and%20other%20team%20outings%20may%20pick%20up%20as%20employees%20work%20from%20the%20office%20more%20frequently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20still%20accountable%20at%20business%20social%20events%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Senning.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20still%20your%20colleagues%20and%20your%20coworkers%2C%20and%20you%20want%20to%20be%20aware%20that%20those%20relationships%20will%20still%20exist%20the%20next%20day%20in%20those%20work%20and%20professional%20environments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20feel%20pressured%20to%20drink%20or%20to%20need%20to%20explain%20your%20reason%20for%20teetotaling.%20For%20those%20who%20are%20drinking%2C%20it%20can%20be%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20stick%20with%20the%20one-drink%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEnjoy%20the%20conversation%2C%20interact%20with%20your%20coworkers%2C%20and%20know%20when%20it's%20time%20to%20go%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Richey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f06acc36-3509-4396-9753-e69d70d86b8f%5C%22%3E'Every%20interaction%20counts'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20etiquette%20guidance%20far%20predates%20the%20pandemic%20and%20may%20hold%20up%20just%20as%20long%20after%3A%20Avoid%20sensitive%20topics%20like%20religion%20or%20overly%20personal%20matters%2C%20as%20well%20as%20swearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20in%20your%20best%20interest%20to%20steer%20clear%20of%20gossip%2C%20Clise%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTypically%20when%20someone%20gossips%20with%20us%2C%20they%20gossip%20about%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20can%20create%20an%20environment%20where%20you%20don't%20feel%20safe%20because%20you're%20not%20sure%20who%20you%20can%20trust%20and%20people%20are%20talking%20about%20other%20people%20beyond%20their%20backs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20good%20rule%20of%20thumb%20is%20to%20remember%20that%20%26quot%3Bevery%20interaction%20counts%2C%20whether%20it's%20a%20virtual%20meeting%2C%20an%20email%2C%20or%20an%20in-person%20interaction%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Richey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Clise%2C%20it's%20about%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20really%20self-aware%20and%20realizing%20that%20work%20is%20not%20just%20us%2C%20it's%20a%20team.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20be%20sure%20we're%20being%20helpful%20and%20encouraging%20others%20to%20share%20their%20thoughts%2C%20to%20feel%20that%20they%20belong%2C%20that%20they're%20included%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20coming%20in%20thinking%2C%20'Oh%2C%20it's%20just%20me%20and%20I'm%20just%20doing%20my%20job.'%20It's%20all%20a%20team%20effort.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20it's%20true%20many%20employees%20%26quot%3Bcould%20use%20a%20little%20polishing%26quot%3B%20on%20their%20soft%20skills%20coming%20out%20of%20a%20long%20period%20of%20remote%20work%20and%20social%20isolation%2C%20says%20Senning%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20really%20comforting%20to%20know%20that%20while%20these%20skills%20can%20deteriorate%2C%20they%20also%20come%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkplace-etiquette-tips-how-to-behave-return-to-office-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738576501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679d4a27bfebcc4d029d708a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busines