e-order-pardon-january-6-participants-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECapitol%20riot%20participants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20chaotic%20back-and-forth%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-house-rolls-back-federal-grant-freeze-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efunding%20freeze%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20immigration%2C%20the%20president%20is%20moving%20swiftly%2C%20cracking%20down%20on%20immigrants%20who%20entered%20the%20United%20States%20illegally.%20While%20all%20these%20moves%20have%20attracted%20copious%20attention%2C%20flying%20under%20the%20radar%20so%20far%20is%20one%20industry%20that%20stands%20to%20see%20a%20major%20windfall%20as%20Trump's%20plans%20fall%20into%20place%3A%20private%20prisons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20president%20signed%20a%20barrage%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-day-one-agenda-executive-orders-inauguration-day-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexecutive%20orders%20and%20actions%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20his%20first%20day%20in%20office.%20Among%20them%3A%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fpresidential-actions%2F2025%2F01%2Finitial-rescissions-of-harmful-executive-orders-and-actions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevocation%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20an%20executive%20order%20signed%20by%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20directing%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20not%20to%20renew%20contracts%20with%20private%2C%20for-profit%20prison%20companies%20to%20house%20people%20convicted%20of%20federal%20crimes.%20By%20late%202022%2C%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Prisons%20had%20ended%20all%20its%20contracts%20with%20private%20prisons%2C%20per%20Biden's%20order.%20Now%2C%20under%20Trump%2C%20the%20flip%20has%20been%20switched%20back%20on%20again.%20The%20move%20isn't%20surprising%20%E2%80%94%20for%20a%20decade%2C%20private%20prisons%20have%20been%20in%20a%20bit%20of%20an%20on-again%2C%20off-again%20situation%20with%20the%20DOJ.%20The%20Obama%20administration%20moved%20to%20phase%20them%20out%2C%20Trump%201.0%20reversed%20it%2C%20Biden%20phased%20them%20out%20again%2C%20and%20Trump%20has%20once%20again%20reversed%20that%20decision.%20The%20industry%20anticipated%20as%20much.%20George%20Zoley%2C%20the%20executive%20chairman%20of%20the%20GEO%20Group%2C%20a%20for-profit%20prison%20company%2C%20said%20on%20an%20earnings%20call%20in%20November%20that%20he%20expected%20Trump%20to%20reverse%20all%20of%20Biden's%20orders%20on%20%26quot%3Bday%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20private%20prison%20companies%20won't%20mind%20getting%20business%20back%20from%20the%20BOP%2C%20that's%20really%20not%20where%20the%20opportunity%20is.%20CoreCivic%2C%20another%20major%20US%20private%20prison%20operator%2C%20acknowledged%20in%20an%20investor%20call%20in%202021%20that%20the%20bureau%20didn't%20really%20have%20much%20of%20a%20need%20for%20private%20facilities%20anymore%20since%20the%20federal%20inmate%20population%20had%20declined%20%E2%80%94%20and%20less%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sentencingproject.org%2Freports%2Fprivate-prisons-in-the-united-states%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E10%25%20of%20those%20inmates%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20in%20private%20prisons.%20The%20opportunity%20is%20Trump's%20plans%20for%20the%20mass%20detention%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-first-day-immigration-executive-orders-deportations-border-visas-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeportation%20of%20immigrants%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Both%20Democratic%20and%20Republican%20administrations%20kept%20up%20work%20with%20for-profit%20prisons%20on%20immigration%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Biden%20administration%2C%20for%20example%2C%20deported%20more%20people%20than%20Trump's%20first%20administration%20did%20and%20often%20detained%20those%20people%20in%20private%20prison%20facilities.%20But%20Trump%20says%20he%20plans%20to%20really%20ramp%20things%20up%20now%2C%20moving%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20migrants%20through%20the%20system%20in%20a%20way%20that%20would%20be%20a%20huge%20boon%20for%20the%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%2C%20to%20us%2C%20an%20unprecedented%20opportunity%20to%20assist%20the%20federal%20government%20and%20the%20incoming%20Trump%20administration%20towards%20achieving%20a%20much%20more%20aggressive%20immigration%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20Zoley%20said%20on%20the%20earnings%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20going%20relatively%20unnoticed%20in%20the%20opening%20days%20of%20the%20administration%2C%20private%20prison%20companies%20are%20a%20secret%20weapon%20for%20the%20president%20in%20his%20war%20on%20immigrants%2C%20and%20they%20stand%20to%20reap%20some%20major%20profits%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20average%20American%20may%20not%20be%20aware%20of%20how%20good%20Trump's%20immigration%20plans%20might%20be%20for%20private%20prisons%2C%20Wall%20Street%20certainly%20is.%20The%20stock%20prices%20of%20GEO%20and%20CoreCivic%20have%20soared%20by%20105%25%20and%2050%25%20since%20the%202024%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20that%20really%20has%20driven%20the%20stock%20price%20since%20the%20election%20basically%20is%20Trump's%20stance%20that%20he's%20going%20to%20deport%20millions%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Joe%20Gomes%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20of%20equity%20research%20at%20Noble%20Capital%20Markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20main%20areas%20in%20which%20the%20private%20prison%20companies%20stand%20to%20make%20money%20on%20Trump's%20deportation%20plans%2C%20said%20Bianca%20Tylek%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20executive%20director%20of%20Worth%20Rises%2C%20a%20group%20that%20advocates%20against%20the%20commercialization%20of%20the%20criminal%20legal%20system.%20One%20is%20detention%2C%20as%20in%20holding%20migrants%20in%20facilities%20until%20their%20court%20hearings%20or%20until%20they're%20expelled%20from%20the%20country.%20The%20second%20is%20surveillance%20of%20migrants%20who%20aren't%20detained%2C%20and%20the%20third%20is%20transportation%20around%2C%20and%20possibly%20out%20of%2C%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImmigration%20and%20Customs%20Enforcement%20has%20funding%20to%20maintain%2041%2C500%20beds%20for%20detained%20migrants%2C%20but%20the%20president's%20border%20czar%2C%20Tom%20Homan%2C%20has%20suggested%20he%20needs%20at%20least%20100%2C000%20beds%20to%20carry%20out%20Trump's%20deportation%20plans.%20The%20recently%20enacted%20Laken%20Riley%20Act%20that%20requires%20the%20detention%20of%20migrants%20accused%20of%20crimes%20such%20as%20theft%20could%20necessitate%2060%2C000%20more%20beds.%20Private%20prison%20operators%20will%20be%20key%20to%20helping%20this%20expansion%2C%20though%20they%20won't%20be%20the%20only%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20Trump%20has%20said%20he%20also%20plans%20to%20use%20space%20at%20Guant%C3%A1namo%20Bay%20to%20house%20detainees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGEO%2C%20the%20largest%20contractor%20for%20ICE%2C%20has%20about%2013%2C500%20beds%20for%20migrants%2C%20but%20executives%20said%20it%20was%20well%20positioned%20to%20scale%20up%20to%20more%20than%2031%2C000%20beds%20in%20the%20near%20future.%20Similarly%2C%20CoreCivic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fpolitics%2Fpolicy%2Ftrump-deportation-private-prison-companies-49a18e3e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20could%20get%20its%20capacity%20to%2025%2C000%20beds%20by%20reopening%20facilities%20it%20recently%20closed.%20It%20has%20also%20looked%20into%20sites%20for%20detaining%20families%2C%20and%20its%20CEO%20told%20the%20Journal%20that%20the%20company%20was%20%26quot%3Bvery%20willing%26quot%3B%20to%20discuss%20detaining%20unaccompanied%20children%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGEO%20also%20operates%20ICE's%20Intensive%20Supervision%20Appearance%20Program%2C%20which%20monitors%20migrants%20as%20they%20go%20through%20legal%20proceedings%20as%20an%20alternative%20to%20detention.%20GEO%20says%20that%20about%20182%2C500%20people%20participate%20in%20that%20program%20daily%2C%20but%20that%20number%20could%20grow%20significantly.%20On%20the%20company's%20earnings%20call%2C%20Zoley%20said%20GEO%20believes%20it%20has%20the%20technology%20and%20resources%20to%20scale%20up%20the%20ISAP%20contract%20to%20%26quot%3Bseveral%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20and%20upward%20to%20several%20millions%20of%20participants.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2011%20million%20people%20are%20thought%20to%20be%20living%20in%20the%20US%20illegally.%20Gomes%20said%20that%20if%20the%20government%20were%20to%20monitor%20a%20certain%20percentage%20of%20those%20people%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20positive%26quot%3B%20for%20GEO%20and%20could%20bring%20in%20others%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BIf%20that%20contract%20got%20extremely%20big%2C%20there%20would%20potentially%20be%20other%20players%20like%20CoreCivic%20that%20could%20potentially%20also%20benefit%20from%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20transportation%20end%2C%20private%20prison%20companies%20contract%20with%20ICE%20to%20move%20migrants%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20in%20the%20air.%20GEO%20said%20on%20its%20earnings%20call%20that%20it%20expects%20its%20air%20subcontracting%20services%20to%20generate%20%2425%20million%20in%20annualized%20revenue%20and%20that%20it%20believes%20it%20could%20scale%20if%20need%20be%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20a%20GEO%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20was%20investing%20%2470%20million%20toward%20%26quot%3Bincreased%20housing%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20monitoring%20capabilities%20and%20services%20to%20meet%20the%20anticipated%20requirements%20of%20the%20federal%20government's%20immigration%20law%20enforcement%20priorities.%26quot%3B%20A%20CoreCivic%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bstays%20in%20regular%20contact%20with%20ICE%20and%20all%20our%20government%20partners%20to%20understand%20their%20changing%20needs%2C%20and%20we%20work%20within%20their%20established%20procurement%20processes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20an%20accident%20that%20the%20private%20prison%20companies%20wound%20up%20in%20this%20situation.%20For%20years%20they've%20been%20hard%20at%20work%20buttering%20up%20public%20officials%2C%20lobbying%2C%20and%20making%20campaign%20donations%2C%20especially%20to%20Trump%20and%20other%20Republicans.%20While%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-business-leaders-donate-million-trump-inaguration-altman-zuckerberg-bezos-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecorporate%20executives%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20come%20around%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20wooing%20Trump%20in%20his%20second%20term%2C%20the%20private%20prisons%20were%20there%20all%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202016%20election%2C%20GEO%20donated%20%24225%2C000%20to%20the%20pro-Trump%20super%20PAC%20Rebuilding%20America%20Now%20through%20a%20subsidiary.%20(The%20advocacy%20group%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeo-group-may-have-illegally-funded-a-trump-super-pac-2016-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Campaign%20Legal%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20a%20complaint%20with%20the%20Federal%20Election%20Commission%2C%20saying%20the%20money%20violated%20a%20ban%20on%20political%20contributions%20by%20federal%20contractors%2C%20but%20that%20was%20dismissed%20because%20of%20a%20deadlock%20on%20the%20FEC.)%20GEO%20and%20CoreCivic%20each%20gave%20%24250%2C000%20to%20Trump's%202016%20inauguration.%20GEO%20held%20its%20annual%20conference%20in%202017%20at%20the%20Trump%20National%20Doral%20Golf%20Club%20in%20Miami%2C%20and%20one%20GEO%20executive%20who%20lobbied%20the%20Trump%20administration%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailybeast.com%2Fprivate-prison-executive-at-geo-group-pursues-federal-funds-spends-at-trump-hotel%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estayed%20at%20Trump's%20hotel%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Pam%20Bondi%2C%20Trump's%20new%20attorney%20general%2C%20lobbied%20for%20GEO%20as%20recently%20as%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%202024%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.citizensforethics.org%2Freports-investigations%2Fcrew-investigations%2Fprivate-prison-behemoth-is-first-corporation-to-max-out-to-trump%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGEO%20maxed%20out%20its%20donation%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Trump's%20campaign%20and%20gave%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20to%20the%20Trump-affiliated%20super%20PAC%20Make%20America%20Great%20Again%20Inc.%20Individual%20executives%20at%20GEO%20and%20CoreCivic%20have%20made%20large%20donations%20to%20Trump%20and%20affiliated%20PACs%20as%20well.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FUS%2Fprivate-prison-firms-contributed-1m-trumps-reelection-now%2Fstory%3Fid%3D116046776%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EABC%20News%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20private%20prison%20companies%20donated%20more%20than%20%241%20million%20to%20Trump's%20reelection%2C%20and%20now%20they're%20hoping%20all%20their%20efforts%20pay%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can%20assume%2C%20given%20their%20exuberance%20after%20the%20election%2C%20that%20they%20are%20really%20excited%20about%20the%20possibilities%20for%20making%20money%20and%20expanding%20the%20'demand'%20that%20will%20be%20going%20up%20for%20them%20and%20their%20services%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Setareh%20Ghandehari%2C%20the%20advocacy%20director%20at%20the%20Detention%20Watch%20Network%2C%20an%20advocacy%20group%20that%20opposes%20immigration%20detention.%20She%20added%2C%20however%2C%20that%20expanding%20detention%20capacity%20isn't%20something%20the%20administration%20can%20achieve%20overnight.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20take%20time%20to%20build%20the%20infrastructure%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20plans%20won't%20just%20take%20time%20%E2%80%94%20they'll%20also%20take%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20money.%20Companies%20such%20as%20GEO%20and%20CoreCivic%20are%20hoping%20to%20get%20a%20cut%20of%20that%20cash%2C%20but%20it's%20unclear%20where%20exactly%20it%20would%20come%20from.%20Even%20before%20the%20president%20took%20office%2C%20ICE%20was%20facing%20a%20%24230%20million%20budget%20shortfall%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Finvestigations%2Fice-budget-shortage-delay-trumps-mass-deportation-plans-rcna184677%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENBC%20News%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20two%20US%20officials.%20To%20execute%20Trump's%20immigration%20plans%2C%20the%20administration%20could%20move%20money%20around%20within%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20from%20places%20such%20as%20the%20Cybersecurity%20and%20Infrastructure%20Security%20Agency%2C%20the%20Coast%20Guard%2C%20and%20the%20Federal%20Emergency%20Management%20Agency.%20It%20may%20also%20pull%20in%20other%20agencies%20for%20assistance.%20But%20ultimately%20it%20would%20need%20Congress%20to%20appropriate%20more%20money%20toward%20its%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20also%20a%20huge%20tax%20on%20taxpayers%2C%26quot%3B%20Tylek%20said.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20entire%20business%20is%20reliant%20on%20the%20government%20paying%20for%20more%20people%20to%20be%20incarcerated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPJ%20Lechleitner%2C%20who%20served%20as%20the%20ICE%20director%20under%20Biden%20and%20spent%2020%20years%20at%20DHS%2C%20said%20that%20adding%2010%2C000%20to%2015%2C000%20beds%20in%20a%20few%20months%20was%20feasible%2C%20%26quot%3Bperhaps%20twice%20that%20many.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20numbers%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20floating%2C%20he%20said%2C%20would%20require%20%26quot%3Byears%20of%20infrastructure%20for%20the%20high-end%20estimate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20they're%20going%20to%20aggressively%20continue%20to%20pursue%20this%2C%20which%20I%20have%20every%20indication%20that%20they%20are%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20need%20a%20lot%20more%20money%20and%20find%20places%20to%20put%20these%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Lechleitner%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20every%20dollar%20is%20approved%2C%20building%20new%20facilities%20takes%20time.%20That%20may%20force%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20employ%20the%20practice%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bcatch%20and%20release%2C%26quot%3B%20Rick%20Su%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%2C%20told%20me.%20While%20it%20may%20not%20be%20exactly%20what%20Trump%20had%20in%20mind%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20deal%20for%20private%20prison%20companies%2C%20which%20will%20be%20eager%20and%20able%20to%20help%20with%20migrant%20monitoring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20your%20position%20on%20immigration%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20criminal%20detention%20being%20a%20commercial%20enterprise%20is%20uncomfortable.%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20best%20for%20my%20shareholders%26quot%3B%20does%20not%20always%20align%20with%20what's%20best%20for%20the%20community%20or%20country%20or%20public%20safety.%20Also%20uncomfortable%20is%20the%20way%20the%20stocks%20of%20private%20prison%20companies%20seem%20to%20ping-pong%20based%20on%20which%20party%20is%20in%20the%20White%20House.%20Back%20in%202016%2C%20private%20prison%20stocks%20crashed%20when%20Hillary%20Clinton%20had%20a%20good%20debate%20performance.%20Though%2C%20for%20what%20it's%20worth%2C%20these%20companies%20have%20fared%20quite%20well%20under%20administrations%20of%20both%20political%20stripes%20%E2%80%94%20both%20Democrats%20and%20Republicans%20have%20employed%20them%20for%20various%20immigration-related%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoth%20the%20Obama%20administration's%20and%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20relationships%20to%20private%20prisons%20set%20some%20guardrails%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Matt%20Nelson%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20Presente%2C%20a%20national%20civil%20and%20human%20rights%20organization%2C%20but%20neither%20addressed%20the%20federal%20govern